30-day payment terms are standard, but late payment interest could be capped lower for Client’s benefit.
Work-for-hire is favorable, but ownership is contingent on full payment, which could delay Client’s rights even for partial payments.
License is perpetual and royalty-free, but limited to use "solely as part of the Deliverables," which may restrict Client’s flexibility.
Requires payment for all Services and expenses, but does not specify rights to partially completed Deliverables or transition assistance.
Disclaimer is broad and could undermine express warranties.
Requires negotiation, then litigation in Texas. No mediation/arbitration option and jurisdiction is unfavorable.
Allows assignment to affiliates or in connection with M&A, but does not require notice to the non-assigning party.
